com.unvired.chyme.api

Class WebEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.unvired.chyme.api.WebEvent

  • public class WebEvent
extends java.lang.Object
    The WebEvent class is an abstraction of a business event or trigger generated in any system capable of http(s) communication. A WebEvent is the data collected by a REST endpoint in Chyme that an external system can use to invoke to indicate an event at the source.

    An Web event has the following components.

    • System ID - ID of the external system generating the event
    • Header Parameters - Header parameters of the REST endpoint invocation
    • Post/Query Parameters - Query or Post parameters of the REST endpoint invocation
    • Body - Content from the message body of the REST endpoint invocation
